The paper proposes a new method for learning latent representations from high dimensional data by taking into account the correlation structure between data points. This is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, given that the paper focuses on learning latent representations, and specifically on the use of Variational Auto-Encoders (VAEs), it is most likely to be classified under cs.LG.
